snippet.textDisplay:
OK, a couple of things:


1. That Californians reference damn near killed me! 🤣
2. Cliff being in prison before - great catch!
3. Respect > Consistency. Absolutely. I couldn't give two shits about inserting DiCaprio in The Great Escape, but Once Upon a Time was about the tragic end of Sharon Tate, as much as it was about stunt doubles in Hollywood. I'm pretty sure Tarantino was making a point by not replacing Sharon with Robbie in The Wrecking Crew, even though he obviously could. Come to think of it, I'm pretty sure he deliberately inserted Leo in The Great Escape just to show us he could, so that keeping Sharon in The Wrecking Crew would hit even harder. QT's a goddamn genius is what he is! God bless him for creating a universe, where Sharon gets a happy ending. 🙁
